  "local_port": 56146,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why do I see numbers and not contacts' names? In WhatsApp?",
  "response": "I'm sorry you're experiencing this issue with WhatsApp. When contact names aren't displaying and you're only seeing phone numbers, it can be frustrating. This problem can stem from several factors. Here's a comprehensive guide to help you troubleshoot and resolve the issue:\n\n### 1. **Check WhatsApp's Permission to Access Contacts**\n\nWhatsApp requires permission to access your phone's contacts to display names correctly.\n\n- **For Android:**\n  1. Go to **Settings** on your phone.\n  2. Navigate to **Apps** or **Applications**.\n  3. Find and select **WhatsApp**.\n  4. Tap on **Permissions**.\n  5. Ensure that **Contacts** permission is **Enabled**.\n\n- **For iOS (iPhone):**\n  1. Open the **Settings** app.\n  2. Scroll down and tap on **WhatsApp**.\n  3. Ensure the **Contacts** toggle is **On**.\n\n### 2. **Refresh Your Contacts in WhatsApp**\n\nSometimes, WhatsApp needs to refresh its contact list to display names correctly.\n\n- Open **WhatsApp**.\n- Tap on the **Chats** tab.\n- Tap the **New Chat** icon (usually a chat bubble with a pencil).\n- Then, tap the **Menu** (three dots) in the top right corner.\n- Select **Refresh**.\n\n### 3. **Ensure Contacts Are Saved Correctly**\n\nVerify that the contacts are saved with the correct phone numbers and country codes.\n\n- Open your phone's **Contacts** app.\n- Check that each contact has the correct number, including the **country code**.\n- Ensure there are no duplicate entries or formatting issues.\n\n### 4. **Sync Your Contacts**\n\nMake sure your phone's contacts are properly synced, especially if you're using services like Google Contacts or iCloud.\n\n- **For Android:**\n  1. Go to **Settings**.\n  2. Tap on **Accounts**.\n  3. Select your account (e.g., Google).\n  4. Ensure **Contacts** syncing is enabled.\n  5. You can also tap **Sync now** to force a sync.\n\n- **For iOS (iPhone):**\n  1. Open **Settings**.\n  2. Tap on your **Apple ID** at the top.\n  3. Select **iCloud**.\n  4. Ensure **Contacts** is toggled **On**.\n\n### 5. **Update WhatsApp to the Latest Version**\n\nUsing an outdated version of WhatsApp might cause display issues.\n\n- **For Android:**\n  1. Open **Google Play Store**.\n  2. Search for **WhatsApp**.\n  3. If an update is available, tap **Update**.\n\n- **For iOS (iPhone):**\n  1. Open the **App Store**.\n  2. Tap on your **Profile** icon.\n  3. Scroll to see if **WhatsApp** has an update and tap **Update** if available.\n\n### 6. **Clear WhatsApp Cache (Android Only)**\n\nClearing the cache can resolve temporary glitches.\n\n1. Go to **Settings**.\n2. Navigate to **Apps** > **WhatsApp**.\n3. Tap on **Storage**.\n4. Select **Clear Cache**.\n\n*Note: This won't delete your chats or media.*\n\n### 7. **Reinstall WhatsApp**\n\nIf none of the above steps work, reinstalling WhatsApp might help. **Ensure you back up your chats before proceeding.**\n\n1. **Back Up Chats:**\n   - Open **WhatsApp**.\n   - Go to **Settings** > **Chats** > **Chat Backup**.\n   - Tap **Back Up** to save your chats to Google Drive (Android) or iCloud (iOS).\n\n2. **Uninstall WhatsApp:**\n   - **Android:** Press and hold the WhatsApp icon and select **Uninstall**.\n   - **iOS:** Press and hold the WhatsApp icon, tap **Remove App**, then **Delete App**.\n\n3. **Reinstall WhatsApp:**\n   - Download WhatsApp from the **Google Play Store** or **App Store**.\n   - Open the app and follow the on-screen setup instructions.\n   - Restore your chat backup when prompted.\n\n### 8. **Check for System Updates**\n\nEnsure your device's operating system is up to date, as outdated software can cause compatibility issues.\n\n- **For Android:**\n  1. Go to **Settings**.\n  2. Scroll down to **System** > **Advanced** > **System Update**.\n  3. Check for updates and install if available.\n\n- **For iOS (iPhone):**\n  1. Open **Settings**.\n  2. Tap **General** > **Software Update**.\n  3. Install any available updates.\n\n### 9. **Ensure Proper Network Connection**\n\nSometimes, a poor internet connection can cause synchronization issues.\n\n- Verify that your device is connected to a stable Wi-Fi or mobile data network.\n- Try toggling Airplane mode on and off to reset network connections.\n\n### 10. **Contact WhatsApp Support**\n\nIf you've tried all the above steps and the issue persists, it might be a specific problem with your account or device. Contact WhatsApp Support for further assistance:\n\n- Open **WhatsApp**.\n- Go to **Settings** > **Help** > **Contact Us**.\n- Describe your issue in detail and submit the request.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n\n- **Group Chats:** If the issue is only with group chats where participants' names aren't showing, ensure all members have saved each other's numbers correctly.\n  \n- **Privacy Settings:** Check if any privacy settings are preventing contact visibility, although WhatsApp doesn't typically offer such specific settings.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to identify and resolve why WhatsApp is displaying numbers instead of contact names. If the problem continues, reaching out to WhatsApp Support is recommended, as they can provide more tailored assistance based on your account and device specifics.",
